definitions.definition: An other, another (person, etc), more often rendered as another .
examples: I'm afraid little Robbie does not always play well with others .

definitions.definition: The other one; the second of two.
examples: One boat is not better than the other .
Why not tell one or other of your parents?

main_definition: An other, another (person, etc), more often rendered as another .
secondary_definitions: The other one; the second of two.
